 Tipperary and Kilkenny."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Miles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Norman origin but uncertain derivation. Unlike most Norman names it is, as far as can be ascertained, not derived from any known Old French or Germanic name element. It may be a greatly altered pet form of   Michael  , which came to be associated with the Latin word <i>miles</i> ‘soldier’ because of the military attributes of the archangel Michael. However, the usual Latin form of the name in the Middle Ages was <i>Milo</i>. There is a common Slavic name element <i>mil</i> ‘grace, favour’, with which it may possibly have some connection. The name has been in regular use in England since the 16th century.  See also  Milo   and   Myles ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Miles Stapleton was born in 1408. He had at least 1 daughter with Catherine De La Pole."},"et":{"1408–":"1408–Surnud","1416–Female":"1416–Surnud","1430–Female":"1430–Surnud","1408–Male":"1408–Surnud","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","1416":"1416"},"fi":{"1408–":"1408–Kuollut","1416–Female":"1416–Kuollut","1430–Female":"1430–Kuollut","1408–Male":"1408–Kuollut","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","1416":"1416"},"fr":{"1408–":"1408–Décédé","1416–Female":"1416–Décédée","1430–Female":"1430–Décédée","1408–Male":"1408–Décédé","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","1416":"1416","lifeSummary":"Miles Stapleton est né en 1408. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Catherine De La Pole."},"de":{"1408–":"1408–Verstorben","1416–Female":"1416–Verstorben","1430–Female":"1430–Verstorben","1408–Male":"1408–Verstorben","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","1416":"1416","lifeSummary":"Miles Stapleton wurde 1408 geboren. Er hatte mit Catherine De La Pole mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1408–":"1408–Desede","1416–Female":"1416–Desede","1430–Female":"1430–Desede","1408–Male":"1408–Desede","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","1416":"1416"},"hu":{"1408–":"1408–elhunyt","1416–Female":"1416–elhuny